hey folks: sorry to have dropped the ball on this. I will look into the issue and update it by this week. 
@scxwhite : I see you are also reporting an issue w/ clustering. Can you file a new issue may be just so we don't miss out.
Can you update w/ all hoodie write configs you use (whether inline or async clustering) as well and which table type etc when you create the ticket. and thanks a lot for given steps to reproduce.

@SabyasachiDasTR : thanks for the update. 
I can't think of a way to fix an existing table (i.e. to dedup). Unfortunately you may have to rebootstrap the entire table. sorry about that. 
@prashantwason : user claims that with hudi 0.9.0, using SIMPLE index and metadata enabled results in duplicate data. but if they use BLOOM index w/ metadata enabled, things are working fine. Do you happened to know of any intricacies w/ SIMPLE index w/ metadata table.

@LucassLin 
Do you also use local docker to produce this problem？  
@nsivabalan  yes，i can reproduce this problem by docker.   It's very strange that I can't reproduce this problem in our product environment,  the only difference is that we use spark3.1 in our env.  i will check it deep tomorrow

@todd5167 I create a mor table, and insert some data, but i can reproduce this issues. can you give the complete sqls please?

the codes that i test like this:
```
create table hudi_mor_tbl (uuid long, name string, order_date string) using hudi partitioned by (order_date) tblproperties (type='mor');
insert into hudi_mor_tbl values (5,'todd', '20220209');
insert into hudi_mor_tbl partition(order_date = '20220210') values (6,'todd');
insert into hudi_mor_tbl_rt partition(order_date = '20220210') values (7,'todd'); -- this use the rt table.
```

@megha2411 : would you mind posting the contents of .hoodie. it does not contain any user data, just the timeline files pertaining to the hudi table. 
Either you can zip and share it here or you can do "ls" and paste the output here. But do ensure you sort it based on FileModTime when you perform "ls". 

And if you can enable debug logs for hudi and share us what you see when you encounter the issue again, would help us triage the issue as well.

